I spoke in the national chapel. The national minister opened the meeting with prayer and singing. I spoke for nearly two hours with much freedom 


                                    -375- 

while the people listened with the greatest attention. There was not one who was asleep or uneasy.--Ms 29, 1887, p. 3. ("Labors in Switzerland," No. 8, diary, January 1 to May 15, 1887.)
